-- Man arrested in London in UBS case
-- 
-- Thu Sep 15, 2011 5:37am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/09/15/us-ubs-london-arrest-idUSTRE78E1NJ20110915

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - London police have arrested a man on suspicion of fraud in connection with a $2 billion trading loss at Swiss investment bank UBS, police sources said on Thursday. 

 City of London police confirmed they had arrested a 31-year-old man in central London at 3:30 a.m. (10:30 p.m. ET on Wednesday) on "suspicion of fraud by abuse of position." They said he remains in police custody while investigations continue. (Reporting by  Stefano Ambrogi )